thread.title: One in hospital after vehicle slips into water near Ashbridges Bay
thread.title_full: One in hospital after vehicle slips into water near Ashbridges Bay

author: Daniyah Yaqoob
title: One in hospital after vehicle slips into water near Ashbridges Bay
text:
A man was sent to the hospital after a vehicle “slid” into the water near Ashbridges Bay.
Police said they responded to a call at 9:42 p.m. about a hazard near Lake Shore Boulevard East and Ashbridges Bay Park Road.
The vehicle was “almost fully” submerged in the water, police said.
A man was sent to the hospital after a vehicle “slid” into the water near Ashbridges Bay.
Police said they responded to a call at 9:42 p.m. about a hazard near Lake Shore Boulevard East and Ashbridges Bay Park Road.
At the scene, a vehicle had slid off the road and was “almost fully” submerged in water, according to a police post on X.
The vehicle had three occupants, police said, who were all able to get out before police arrived at the scene.
One man was transported to the hospital with minor injuries, police said.
The vehicle slid near a docking area, according to police, though they did not say how it slid.
Daniyah Yaqoob is a staff reporter with the Toronto Star. She
